      <section eId="sec_CHC-1281-4">
        <num>CHC 1281.4</num>
        <heading>1281.4.  Types of adoption</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1281-4__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>This Title sets forth the exclusive procedures for intercountry adoption of foreign orphans in Louisiana.  There are two types of intercountry adoptions of foreign orphans in Louisiana:</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1281-4__subsec_A__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Adoption or recognition of a foreign decree of adoption of a foreign orphan from a country outside the United States that is not a party to the Hague Adoption Convention.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="CHC-1281-4__subsec_A__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Adoption or recognition of a foreign decree of adoption of a convention adoptee from a country outside the United States that is a party to the Hague Adoption Convention.</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1281-4__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The procedures governing each type of adoption are set forth in the following Articles.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
